OL,5, BBC director general Tim Davie has     
OL,6, apologised to licence fee payers after 
OL,7, a day of sports programme disruption.  
OL,9,FFootball shows were pulled at the last 
OL,10,Fminute on Saturday after presenters and
OL,11,Fcommentators walked out in support of  
OL,12,FMatch of the Day host Gary Lineker.    
OL,14,FMatch of the Day was reduced to a      
OL,15,F20-minute edition.                     
OL,17,FLineker was suspended after criticising
OL,18,Fthe government's controversial asylum  
OL,19,Fpolicy. But Mr Davie denied the        
OL,20,Fgovernment pressured him into the move.
